    },
    {
      "title": "B. Plural definite (theSUPR)",
      "instructions": "The plural definite \"the hobbits\" uses the supremum iota: Œπx.[‚àóhobbit(x) ‚àß ‚àÄy[‚àóhobbit(y)‚Üíy‚â§x]] ‚Äî the maximal sum of all hobbits. theSUPR ‚Üù ŒªX.Œπx.[X(x) ‚àß ‚àÄy[X(y)‚Üíy‚â§x]] takes the plural predicate (‚àóhobbit) and returns its supremum ‚Äî an individual of type e.",
      "items": [
        {
          "sentence": "the hobbits",
          "tree": "[.DP [.D theSUPR ] [.NP hobbits ] ]",
          "targets": [
            "Œπx.[‚àóhobbit(x) ‚àß ‚àÄy[‚àóhobbit(y) ‚Üí y‚â§x]]"
